        "sourceCoverage": "partial"
      },
      "score": 18,
      "summary": "This page defines the next product track: turn Dendrite Wiki MCP from a wiki-first documentation tool into the best project-local memory companion for AI coding agents, while keeping the wiki accurate and readable for humans.",
      "reasons": [
        "content mentions \"wiki\"",
        "claim text matches \"wiki\"",
        "2 inbound links"
      ],
      "matchedTerms": [
        "wiki"
      ],
      "claimMatches": [
        {
          "text": "Dendrite Wiki MCP now implements a project-local memory store with remember, handoff capture, recall, forget, review, promotion, exact-duplicate cleanup, near-duplicate grouping, and contradiction review, while `wiki_context` now carries recent handoffs into the next session.",
          "status": "current",
          "sources": [
            {
              "kind": "wiki",
              "label": "Architecture",
              "slug": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "kind": "wiki",
              "label": "Project Log",
              "slug": "project-log"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "The `dendrite-wiki recall:bootstrap` CLI now scaffolds `local-data/recall-probes.json` from the current memory store, emitting one portable probe per active non-handoff memory (using its summary as the query and its tags, related files, and related pages as matchers; machine-local IDs are intentionally omitted) and falling back to a documented placeholder template when the store is empty. The command refuses to overwrite an existing file unless `--force` is passed and accepts `--output` for a custom destination.",
          "status": "current",
          "sources": [
            {
